<div class="c310_3">
<div id="v310.3.1"><span class="H1397 s">I <i>am</i> the man</span><span class="H7200 s"> <i>that</i> hath seen</span><span class="H6040 s"> affliction</span><span class="H7626 s"> by the rod</span><span class="H5678 s"> of his wrath</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.2"><span class="H5090 s">He hath led</span><span class="H3212 s"> me, and brought</span><span class="H2822 s"> <i>me into</i> darkness</span><span class="H216 s">, but not <i>into</i> light</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.3"><span class="H7725 s">Surely against me is he turned</span><span class="H2015 s">; he turneth</span><span class="H3027 s"> his hand</span><span class="H3117 s"> <i>against me</i> all the day</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.4"><span class="H1320 s">My flesh</span><span class="H5785 s"> and my skin</span><span class="H1086 s"> hath he made old</span><span class="H7665 s">; he hath broken</span><span class="H6106 s"> my bones</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.5"><span class="H1129 s">He hath builded against</span><span class="H5362 s"> me, and compassed</span><span class="H7219 s"> <i>me</i> with gall</span><span class="H8513 s"> and travail</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.6"><span class="H3427 s">He hath set</span><span class="H4285 s"> me in dark places</span><span class="H4191 s">, as <i>they that be</i> dead</span><span class="H5769 s"> of old</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.7"><span class="H1443 s">He hath hedged</span><span class="H3318 s"> me about, that I cannot get out</span><span class="H5178 s">: he hath made my chain</span><span class="H3513 s"> heavy</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.8"><span class="H2199 s">Also when I cry</span><span class="H7768 s"> and shout</span><span class="H5640 s">, he shutteth out</span><span class="H8605 s"> my prayer</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.9"><span class="H1443 s">He hath inclosed</span><span class="H1870 s"> my ways</span><span class="H1496 s"> with hewn stone</span><span class="H5410 s">, he hath made my paths</span><span class="H5753 s"> crooked</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.10"><span class="H1677 s">He <i>was</i> unto me <i>as</i> a bear</span><span class="H693 s"> lying in wait</span><span class="H738 s">, <i>and as</i> a lion</span><span class="H4565 s"> in secret places</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.11"><span class="H5493 s">He hath turned aside</span><span class="H1870 s"> my ways</span><span class="H6582 s">, and pulled me in pieces</span><span class="H7760 s">: he hath made</span><span class="H8074 s"> me desolate</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.12"><span class="H1869 s">He hath bent</span><span class="H7198 s"> his bow</span><span class="H5324 s">, and set</span><span class="H4307 s"> me as a mark</span><span class="H2671 s"> for the arrow</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.13"><span class="H1121 s">He hath caused the arrows</span><span class="H827 s"> of his quiver</span><span class="H935 s"> to enter</span><span class="H3629 s"> into my reins</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (arrows: Heb. sons)</span></div>
<div id="v310.3.14"><span class="H7814 s">I was a derision</span><span class="H5971 s"> to all my people</span><span class="H5058 s">; <i>and</i> their song</span><span class="H3117 s"> all the day</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.15"><span class="H7646 s">He hath filled</span><span class="H4844 s"> me with bitterness</span><span class="H7301 s">, he hath made me drunken</span><span class="H3939 s"> with wormwood</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (bitterness: Heb. bitternesses)</span></div>
<div id="v310.3.16"><span class="H1638 s">He hath also broken</span><span class="H8127 s"> my teeth</span><span class="H2687 s"> with gravel stones</span><span class="H3728 s">, he hath covered</span><span class="H665 s"> me with ashes</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (covered…: or, rolled me in the ashes)</span></div>
<div id="v310.3.17"><span class="H2186 s">And thou hast removed</span><span class="H5315 s"> my soul</span><span class="H2186 s"> far off</span><span class="H7965 s"> from peace</span><span class="H5382 s">: I forgat</span><span class="H2896 s"> prosperity</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (prosperity: Heb. good)</span></div>
<div id="v310.3.18"><span class="H559 s">And I said</span><span class="H5331 s">, My strength</span><span class="H8431 s"> and my hope</span><span class="H6 s"> is perished</span><span class="H3068 s"> from the LORD</span>:</div>
<div id="v310.3.19"><span class="H2142 s">Remembering</span><span class="H6040 s"> mine affliction</span><span class="H4788 s"> and my misery</span><span class="H3939 s">, the wormwood</span><span class="H7219 s"> and the gall</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Remembering: or, Remember)</span></div>
<div id="v310.3.20"><span class="H5315 s">My soul</span><span class="H2142 s"> hath <i>them</i> still</span><span class="H2142 s"> in remembrance</span><span class="H7743 s">, and is humbled</span> in me. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (humbled: Heb. bowed)</span></div>
<div id="v310.3.21"><span class="H7725 s">This I recall</span><span class="H3820 s"> to my mind</span><span class="H3176 s">, therefore have I hope</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (recall…: Heb. make to return to my heart)</span></div>
<div id="v310.3.22"><span class="H3068 s"><i>It is of</i> the LORD'S</span><span class="H2617 s"> mercies</span><span class="H8552 s"> that we are not consumed</span><span class="H7356 s">, because his compassions</span><span class="H3615 s"> fail</span> not.</div>
<div id="v310.3.23"><span class="H2319 s"><i>They are</i> new</span><span class="H1242 s"> every morning</span><span class="H7227 s">: great</span><span class="H530 s"> <i>is</i> thy faithfulness</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.24"><span class="H3068 s">The LORD</span><span class="H2506 s"> <i>is</i> my portion</span><span class="H559 s">, saith</span><span class="H5315 s"> my soul</span><span class="H3176 s">; therefore will I hope</span> in him.</div>
<div id="v310.3.25"><span class="H3068 s">The LORD</span><span class="H2896 s"> <i>is</i> good</span><span class="H6960 s"> unto them that wait</span><span class="H5315 s"> for him, to the soul</span><span class="H1875 s"> <i>that</i> seeketh</span> him.</div>
<div id="v310.3.26"><span class="H2896 s"><i>It is</i> good</span><span class="H3175 s"> that <i>a man</i> should both hope</span><span class="H2342 s"> †</span><span class="H1748 s"> and quietly wait</span><span class="H8668 s"> for the salvation</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.27"><span class="H2896 s"><i>It is</i> good</span><span class="H1397 s"> for a man</span><span class="H5375 s"> that he bear</span><span class="H5923 s"> the yoke</span><span class="H5271 s"> in his youth</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.28"><span class="H3427 s">He sitteth</span><span class="H910 s"> alone</span><span class="H1826 s"> and keepeth silence</span><span class="H5190 s">, because he hath borne</span> <i>it</i> upon him.</div>
<div id="v310.3.29"><span class="H5414 s">He putteth</span><span class="H6310 s"> his mouth</span><span class="H6083 s"> in the dust</span><span class="H3426 s">; if so be there may be</span><span class="H8615 s"> hope</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.30"><span class="H5414 s">He giveth</span><span class="H3895 s"> <i>his</i> cheek</span><span class="H5221 s"> to him that smiteth</span><span class="H7646 s"> him: he is filled full</span><span class="H2781 s"> with reproach</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.31"><span class="H136 s">For the Lord</span><span class="H2186 s"> will not cast off</span><span class="H5769 s"> for ever</span>:</div>
<div id="v310.3.32"><span class="H3013 s">But though he cause grief</span><span class="H7355 s">, yet will he have compassion</span><span class="H7230 s"> according to the multitude</span><span class="H2617 s"> of his mercies</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.33"><span class="H6031 s">For he doth not afflict</span><span class="H3820 s"> willingly</span><span class="H3013 s"> nor grieve</span><span class="H1121 s"> the children</span><span class="H376 s"> of men</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (willingly: Heb. from his heart)</span></div>
<div id="v310.3.34"><span class="H1792 s">To crush</span><span class="H7272 s"> under his feet</span><span class="H615 s"> all the prisoners</span><span class="H776 s"> of the earth</span>,</div>
<div id="v310.3.35"><span class="H5186 s">To turn aside</span><span class="H4941 s"> the right</span><span class="H1397 s"> of a man</span><span class="H6440 s"> before the face</span><span class="H5945 s"> of the most High</span>, <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the most High: or, a superior)</span></div>
<div id="v310.3.36"><span class="H5791 s">To subvert</span><span class="H120 s"> a man</span><span class="H7379 s"> in his cause</span><span class="H136 s">, the Lord</span><span class="H7200 s"> approveth</span> not. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (approveth not: or, seeth not)</span></div>
<div id="v310.3.37"><span class="H559 s">Who <i>is</i> he <i>that</i> saith</span><span class="H136 s">, and it cometh to pass, <i>when</i> the Lord</span><span class="H6680 s"> commandeth</span> <i>it</i> not?</div>
<div id="v310.3.38"><span class="H6310 s">Out of the mouth</span><span class="H5945 s"> of the most High</span><span class="H3318 s"> proceedeth</span><span class="H7451 s"> not evil</span><span class="H2896 s"> and good</span>?</div>
<div id="v310.3.39"><span class="H2416 s">Wherefore doth a living</span><span class="H120 s"> man</span><span class="H596 s"> complain</span><span class="H1397 s">, a man</span><span class="H2399 s"> for the punishment of his sins</span>? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (complain: or, murmur)</span></div>
<div id="v310.3.40"><span class="H2664 s">Let us search</span><span class="H2713 s"> and try</span><span class="H1870 s"> our ways</span><span class="H7725 s">, and turn again</span><span class="H3068 s"> to the LORD</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.41"><span class="H5375 s">Let us lift up</span><span class="H3824 s"> our heart</span><span class="H3709 s"> with <i>our</i> hands</span><span class="H410 s"> unto God</span><span class="H8064 s"> in the heavens</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.42"><span class="H5168 s">We</span><span class="H6586 s"> have transgressed</span><span class="H4784 s"> and have rebelled</span><span class="H5545 s">: thou hast not pardoned</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.43"><span class="H5526 s">Thou hast covered</span><span class="H639 s"> with anger</span><span class="H7291 s">, and persecuted</span><span class="H2026 s"> us: thou hast slain</span><span class="H2550 s">, thou hast not pitied</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.44"><span class="H5526 s">Thou hast covered</span><span class="H6051 s"> thyself with a cloud</span><span class="H8605 s">, that <i>our</i> prayer</span><span class="H5674 s"> should not pass through</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.45"><span class="H7760 s">Thou hast made</span><span class="H5501 s"> us <i>as</i> the offscouring</span><span class="H3973 s"> and refuse</span><span class="H7130 s"> in the midst</span><span class="H5971 s"> of the people</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.46"><span class="H341 s">All our enemies</span><span class="H6475 s"> have opened</span><span class="H6310 s"> their mouths</span> against us.</div>
<div id="v310.3.47"><span class="H6343 s">Fear</span><span class="H6354 s"> and a snare</span><span class="H7612 s"> is come upon us, desolation</span><span class="H7667 s"> and destruction</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.48"><span class="H5869 s">Mine eye</span><span class="H3381 s"> runneth down</span><span class="H6388 s"> with rivers</span><span class="H4325 s"> of water</span><span class="H7667 s"> for the destruction</span><span class="H1323 s"> of the daughter</span><span class="H5971 s"> of my people</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.49"><span class="H5869 s">Mine eye</span><span class="H5064 s"> trickleth down</span><span class="H1820 s">, and ceaseth</span><span class="H2014 s"> not, without any intermission</span>,</div>
<div id="v310.3.50"><span class="H3068 s">Till the LORD</span><span class="H8259 s"> look down</span><span class="H7200 s">, and behold</span><span class="H8064 s"> from heaven</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.51"><span class="H5869 s">Mine eye</span><span class="H5953 s"> affecteth</span><span class="H5315 s"> mine heart</span><span class="H1323 s"> because of all the daughters</span><span class="H5892 s"> of my city</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (mine heart: Heb. my soul) (because…: or, more than all)</span></div>
<div id="v310.3.52"><span class="H341 s">Mine enemies</span><span class="H6679 s"> chased</span><span class="H6679 s"> me sore</span><span class="H6833 s">, like a bird</span><span class="H2600 s">, without cause</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.53"><span class="H6789 s">They have cut off</span><span class="H2416 s"> my life</span><span class="H953 s"> in the dungeon</span><span class="H3034 s">, and cast</span><span class="H68 s"> a stone</span> upon me.</div>
<div id="v310.3.54"><span class="H4325 s">Waters</span><span class="H6687 s"> flowed over</span><span class="H7218 s"> mine head</span><span class="H559 s">; <i>then</i> I said</span><span class="H1504 s">, I am cut off</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.55"><span class="H7121 s">I called</span><span class="H8034 s"> upon thy name</span><span class="H3068 s">, O LORD</span><span class="H8482 s">, out of the low</span><span class="H953 s"> dungeon</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.56"><span class="H8085 s">Thou hast heard</span><span class="H6963 s"> my voice</span><span class="H5956 s">: hide</span><span class="H241 s"> not thine ear</span><span class="H7309 s"> at my breathing</span><span class="H7775 s">, at my cry</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.57"><span class="H7126 s">Thou drewest near</span><span class="H3117 s"> in the day</span><span class="H7121 s"> <i>that</i> I called</span><span class="H559 s"> upon thee: thou saidst</span><span class="H3372 s">, Fear</span> not.</div>
<div id="v310.3.58"><span class="H136 s">O Lord</span><span class="H7378 s">, thou hast pleaded</span><span class="H7379 s"> the causes</span><span class="H5315 s"> of my soul</span><span class="H1350 s">; thou hast redeemed</span><span class="H2416 s"> my life</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.59"><span class="H3068 s">O LORD</span><span class="H7200 s">, thou hast seen</span><span class="H5792 s"> my wrong</span><span class="H8199 s">: judge</span><span class="H4941 s"> thou my cause</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.60"><span class="H7200 s">Thou hast seen</span><span class="H5360 s"> all their vengeance</span><span class="H4284 s"> <i>and</i> all their imaginations</span> against me.</div>
<div id="v310.3.61"><span class="H8085 s">Thou hast heard</span><span class="H2781 s"> their reproach</span><span class="H3068 s">, O LORD</span><span class="H4284 s">, <i>and</i> all their imaginations</span> against me;</div>
<div id="v310.3.62"><span class="H8193 s">The lips</span><span class="H6965 s"> of those that rose up</span><span class="H1902 s"> against me, and their device</span><span class="H3117 s"> against me all the day</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.63"><span class="H5027 s">Behold</span><span class="H3427 s"> their sitting down</span><span class="H7012 s">, and their rising up</span><span class="H4485 s">; I <i>am</i> their musick</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.64"><span class="H7725 s">Render</span><span class="H1576 s"> unto them a recompence</span><span class="H3068 s">, O LORD</span><span class="H4639 s">, according to the work</span><span class="H3027 s"> of their hands</span>.</div>
<div id="v310.3.65"><span class="H5414 s">Give</span><span class="H4044 s"> them sorrow</span><span class="H3820 s"> of heart</span><span class="H8381 s">, thy curse</span> unto them. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (sorrow…: or, obstinacy of heart)</span></div>
<div id="v310.3.66"><span class="H7291 s">Persecute</span><span class="H8045 s"> and destroy</span><span class="H639 s"> them in anger</span><span class="H8064 s"> from under the heavens</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span>.</div></div>
